Hiding a post (basically add a "dontshow = true" to the hidden posts, and filter that out on the front page...)
- https://stackoverflow.com/questions/23935062/jekyll-github-pages-how-to-hide-a-post
- https://gist.github.com/carlo/2870636
- http://hamishwillee.github.io/2014/06/11/public-drafts-in-jekyll/
- https://jekyllrb.com/docs/drafts/

Changing Jekyll home page default (why? See above)
- https://jekyllrb.com/docs/themes/#overriding-theme-defaults

Custom processor / markdown options (for math, see below)
- https://jekyllrb.com/docs/configuration/#custom-markdown-processors
- https://jekyllrb.com/docs/configuration/#markdown-options

Pandoc
- https://github.com/jgm/pandoc/wiki/Pandoc-Extras#static-website-generators
- https://github.com/skade/yakshav.es -- uses Pandoc and looks great

Math
- https://github.com/linjer/jekyll-katex -- requires {% katex %} or {% katex display %}
- https://haixing-hu.github.io/programming/2013/09/20/how-to-use-mathjax-in-jekyll-generated-github-pages/ (says to use maruku; has some tests at the bottom of the page)
- https://xuc.me/blog/katex-and-jekyll/
- http://drz.ac/2013/01/03/blogging-with-math/ (has some great tests at the bottom of the page)
- MathJax output formats: http://docs.mathjax.org/en/latest/output.html (It's clear that CommonHTML is what we want, with HTML+CSS in second place. See also the note about viewport at http://docs.mathjax.org/en/latest/output.html#viewport-meta-tag)
- MathJax font options: http://docs.mathjax.org/en/latest/font-support.html (Demo: https://www.checkmyworking.com/misc/MathJax-play-area/)
- Most promising: https://github.com/jgm/pandoc/issues/3153 (they seem to go on the wrong path trying SVG instead of HTML+CSS. Output is ugly! https://ickc.github.io/pandoc-MathJax-node/)
